Review this section of the User Manual:

http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual/install.html#N1008F

Especially note the part beginning &quot;Note&quot; about the &quot;--bind&quot; flag. 
Without that flag, the administrative webserver only accepts connections 
made locally from the same machine.

Before enabling access from other IPs, you should carefully review and 
understand these sections of the User Manual and wiki about security 
considerations:

http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual/install.html#security

https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/Security+Considerations

In particular for H1, it&#39;s best to not use the &quot;--bind&quot; option, and 
instead use an SSH tunnel to reach the administrative port, to ensure 
that only those who already have local access to the crawling system can 
connect to the administrative interface.

- Gordon @ IA

